    "Name": "J.Edgar",
    "Details": "Looking to update the J. Edgar for the modern battlefield, RISC engineers decided to augment the short-range punch with the option for long-range harassment by swapping the traditional SRMs for Multi-Missile launchers.  This allows the use of LRM ammunition easily, allowing the J. Edgar to utilize its speed to dictate the range of engagement, as well as increasing the SRM missiles launched by 50% when it comes time to close in.  The upgrade from a standard Medium Laser to an X-Pulse Medium laser is a modest updating of old hardware to newer specs.\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Fusion: Expensive engine that works in a Vacuum.</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 11/17 Hex: 330/510 Meters.</color></b>\n\n<color=#ffcc00><b>Armor:</b> Heavy Ferro-Fibrous\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>       150     15\n<b>Left</b>         120     15\n<b>Right</b>       120     15\n<b>Rear</b>        105     15\n<b>Turret</b>      120     15\n\n<b>Total</b>      615     75</color>\n\n<color=#ff0000>Quirk: Accurate Weapon - Laser</color>",
